\section{Objectives}
Considering high complexity and abstraction of object-oriented programming concepts, there is a need for innovative solution, which may serve as mean for learning these concepts.\\
The aim of this Lab Classes Script is the description of developed interactive educational application for object-oriented-programming.\\
The main objective of the proposed project was to create a tool for teaching graduates and specialists in technical study programs and related areas of automation using Unity~\cite{Unity} engine applyed to augmented reality and interactive learning in modelling, simulation and control. Visualization of the modelling and control processes of complex systems, components and devices in virtual and mixed realities will give students more insight and better understand the studied stuff compared with conventional learning methods.~\cite{8337533}\\
The authors built this lab script as self explanatory as possible for basic examples, and a specific application \textcolor{red}{BIM~\cite{BIM} of an eletric cabinet}. The user then creates solutions based on examples, and can build the authors aplication in the end. He then has all the knoledge possible to start building his own application, and to try and answer the challenge proposal exposed in the last section~\ref{challenge}, in which the user creates solution for given problem using the knowledge learnt in this scrip and from other sources, which were presented to him in the introduction part of the application. After the user finishes the challenge, he will have the basic knoledge to build his own AR application.~\cite{9039853}

\textcolor{red}{BIM (Building Information. Modeling) FALAR DISTO}.

\textcolor{red}{CITAR O LIVRO} ~\cite{linowes2021augmented}

